## Core UI Principles

- If you are in agent mode, implement and update code across the codebase as needed to satisfy the request
- Add short documentation comments before classes and public functions: purpose, how to use, and a brief example
- Before non-obvious conditions, explain why the branch exists and how it helps in this snippet
- Use Flutter localization for every user-facing string (`AppLocalizations`)
- Use the Gap package for spacing; define shared gaps in a `GGap` class and use only those
- Define and use `GScaffold`, `GText`, and `GButton` instead of raw `Scaffold` / `Text` / `ElevatedButton` (and similar) in feature UI
- Put all asset paths in an `ImagePath` class and reference paths only from there
- Define colors/typography in the theme (`app_theme`); never use ad-hoc color literals in widgets
- Before using a new color, add or update it in `app_theme`, then consume it from the theme
- Write/update each feature's `README.md` using `readme_structure.mdc`
- Local data sources live in `data/datasources/local/`
- Remote APIs live in `data/datasources/remote/`

### UI Implementation Example
```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_bloc/flutter_bloc.dart';
import 'package:flutter_gen/gen_l10n/app_localizations.dart';
import 'package:project/core/locator.dart';
import 'package:project/core/widgets/g_button.dart';
import 'package:project/core/widgets/g_scaffold.dart';
import 'package:project/core/widgets/g_text.dart';
import 'package:project/core/widgets/g_gap.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/presentation/bloc/login_bloc.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/presentation/bloc/login_event.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/presentation/bloc/login_state.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/presentation/widgets/login_form.dart';
import 'package:project/features/login/presentation/widgets/login_error_view.dart';

/// Main login screen for the login feature.
/// Example: Navigator.pushNamed(context, PageName.login);
class LoginPage extends StatelessWidget {
  final String userId;

  const LoginPage({super.key, required this.userId});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context);

    return BlocProvider(
      create: (_) => locator<LoginBloc>()
        ..add(LoginEvent.login(userId: userId)),
      child: GScaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(
          title: GText(l10n.loginTitle),
          actions: [
            BlocBuilder<LoginBloc, LoginState>(
              builder: (context, state) => IconButton(
                icon: const Icon(Icons.refresh),
                onPressed: () {
                  context.read<LoginBloc>().add(
                        LoginEvent.login(userId: userId),
                      );
                },
              ),
            ),
          ],
        ),
        body: BlocListener<LoginBloc, LoginState>(
          listener: (context, state) {
            state.login.when(
              initial: () {},
              loading: () {},
              completed: (_) {
                ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(
                  SnackBar(content: GText(l10n.loginSuccess)),
                );
              },
              error: (message) {
                ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(
                  SnackBar(content: GText(l10n.loginError(message))),
                );
              },
            );
          },
          child: BlocBuilder<LoginBloc, LoginState>(
            builder: (context, state) => state.login.when(
              initial: () => const SizedBox.shrink(),
              loading: () => const Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator()),
              completed: (user) => LoginForm(user: user),
              error: (message) => LoginErrorView(message: message),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
